Disclaimer: Yahoo does not support this software in any way!! Do not bother
them with questions. 

Send all questions/suggestions/etc to :
	kyim-support@lists.sourceforge.net

Thanks to Philip S Tellis for creating and maintaining libyahoo2. 

Thanks to www.freeaudioclips.com for the sounds clips supplied with
the distribution. The default location for those files on your system
is $KDEDIR/share/apps/kyim/sounds.


============================================================================

THIS VERSION WILL ONLY WORK ON KDE3 and Qt 3.x 

This is a development version. It is the first release on the new libyahoo
code. Currently chat and conferencing should work, file transfers do not 
work. 

Please report all bugs to our database at 

http://kyim.sourceforge.net/download.html 

or email kyim-support@lists.sourceforge.net

To build:
./configure
make
make install

=============================================================================

HOW TO USE:
-----------
To chat: double click on name in buddylist.
To start a conference: Select Yahoo-->New Conference

You can only change options when not logged into Yahoo. 

The "Debug Messages" window will show the raw yahoo packets from yahoolib.

